# Lab 09 — NAT & PAT (Network Address Translation)

## 🎯 Objectives

- Understand why NAT exists and the difference between static NAT, dynamic NAT, and PAT
- Configure static NAT to map a single private IP to a single public IP
- Configure dynamic NAT using a pool of public addresses
- Configure PAT (overload) to allow multiple private hosts to share one public IP
- Define inside/outside interfaces on the router
- Verify translations with `show ip nat translations`

